  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A binding requirement mandates experimental-validation as the verification method for hemolysis QoI; however, the supporting validation activity was carried out as a high-fidelity numerical simulation. The package narrative argues that the simulation replicates physical test conditions with sufficient fidelity to be considered equivalent to bench-top measurement, but the structured activityType field records 'numerical-simulation', creating an inference-method mismatch (W-AR-03). Decision recorded as Accepted based on the narrative argument.",
