      "name": "High-fidelity CFD hemolysis prediction vs. analytical reference — presented as experimental-equivalent validation",
      "description": "A high-resolution LES simulation of the FDA generic centrifugal pump was executed across all 5 operating points. Predicted hemolysis index values were compared against an analytical power-law reference derived from published in-vitro correlations. The assessment team argues that because the simulation boundary conditions were set to precisely replicate the physical test rig geometry and flow rates documented in FDA bench studies, the numerical results carry evidentiary weight equivalent to a direct experimental measurement. Discrepancies between predicted and reference hemolysis index values were within 12% at all operating points, which the team characterises as acceptable given MRL-5 uncertainty budgets.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "Mean absolute percentage error 9.4% across 5 operating points",
