    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the high-fidelity LES simulation replicates FDA bench-test conditions with sufficient geometric and boundary-condition fidelity to serve as an experimental-equivalent validation source. The 9.4% mean absolute error against the analytical reference was judged acceptable within the MRL-5 uncertainty budget. The team noted that the requirement specifies experimental-validation but concluded the simulation campaign satisfies the intent of that requirement. No formal method substitution was documented, and the structured activityType field remains 'numerical-simulation', creating an unresolved inference-method mismatch with the binding requirement's requiredVerificationMethod of 'experimental-validation'.",
